d%20on%20the%20FTC%20to%20%26quot%3Bhold%20the%20companies%20and%20their%20senior%20executives%20responsible%26quot%3B%20if%20they%20broke%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20FTC%20should%20hold%20accountable%20the%20automakers%2C%20which%20shared%20their%20customers'%20data%20with%20data%20brokers%20without%20obtaining%20informed%20consent%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20data%20brokers%2C%20which%20resold%20data%20that%20had%20not%20been%20obtained%20in%20a%20lawful%20manner%2C%26quot%3B%20Democratic%20Senators%20Ron%20Wyden%20and%20Ed%20Markey%20wrote%20in%20their%20letter%20to%20the%20FTC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeneral%20Motors%2C%20Honda%2C%20and%20Hyundai%20each%20shared%20drivers'%20%26quot%3Bacceleration%20and%20braking%20data%26quot%3B%20with%20brokers%2C%20and%20General%20Motors%20%26quot%3Bdisclosed%20customer%20location%20data%26quot%3B%20to%20at%20least%20two%20companies%2C%20the%20senators%20wrote.%20They%20accused%20the%20companies%20of%20not%20seeking%20customer%20consent%20for%20data%20sharing%20or%20using%20murky%20techniques%20to%20get%20drivers%20to%20opt%20in%2C%20like%20implying%20that%20the%20data%20would%20%26quot%3Bonly%20lower%20insurance%20bills%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauto-insurance-monitor-driving-phone-apps-life360-higher-rates-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20raise%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well%2C%20the%20senators%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202021%20call%20with%20Wyden's%20office%2C%20GM%20officials%20said%20it%20had%20been%20sharing%20%26quot%3Bbulk%2C%20de-identified%20location%20data%20from%20GM%20cars%20to%20an%20unnamed%20commercial%20partner%2C%20which%20GM%20officials%20would%20not%20identify.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20that%20oversight%20call%2C%20GM%20confirmed%20it%20did%20not%20seek%20informed%20consent%20from%20consumers%20for%20sharing%20this%20data.%20Company%20officials%20told%20Senator%20Wyden's%20staff%20that%20the%20on